criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Must have provided informed consent in a manner approved by the Investigator's
             Institutional Review Board (IRB) prior to any study-related procedure being performed.
             If a participant is unable to provide informed consent due to his/her medical
             condition, the participant's legally authorized representative may consent on behalf
             of the study participant, as permitted by local law and institutional Standard
             Operating Procedures

          -  Age ≥18 years at the time of informed consent;

          -  In-patient or out-patient referral for CMR imaging;

          -  Referral for suspected acute or chronic cardiomyopathy state(s) of ischemic and/or
             non-ischemic etiology;

          -  Recently drawn (≤180 days) and available serum laboratory markers of hemoglobin,
             hematocrit, and creatinine;

          -  Willing and able to abide by all study requirements

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Standard contraindication(s) to magnetic resonance imaging performance based upon
             local site policies;

          -  Able to breath hold (i.e. real-time cine imaging not supported);

          -  Current or recent (≤ 60 days) pregnancy;

          -  Current or recent (≤ 60 days) sepsis requiring intubation;

          -  Cardiac implantable electronic implanted device (CIED) of any type (excluded due to
             likelihood of reduced image quality and anticipated influence on algorithm
             performance), inclusive of permanent pacemaker, implantable cardioverter defibrillator
             or implantable loop recorder;

          -  Severe aortic valve stenosis (i.e., mean AVG >40 mmHg);

          -  Prosthetic valve (mechanical or bioprosthetic) in mitral or aortic position

          -  Congenital heart disease, inclusive of any surgically-corrected disease, dextrocardia,
             Tetralogy of Fallot, uncorrected partial anomalous pulmonary venous return, or large
             atrial septal defect (Qp:Qs ≥1.5) [Note: bicuspid aortic valve disease is not an
             exclusion criterion in isolation];
